## 2. `buildRouteMap`

**Signature** (from `packages/core/src/routing/route-map/builder.ts`):

```typescript
function buildRouteMap<R extends string, CONTEXT extends CommandContext = CommandContext>({
    routes,
    defaultCommand,
    docs,
    aliases,
}: RouteMapBuilderArguments<R, CONTEXT>): RouteMap<CONTEXT>
```

**`RouteMapBuilderArguments` shape:**
```typescript
{
    routes: Record<R, Command<CONTEXT> | RouteMap<CONTEXT>>,  // at least one required
    defaultCommand?: R,                                        // optional, must be a Command (not a RouteMap)
    docs: {
        brief: string,
        fullDescription?: string,
        hideRoute?: Partial<Record<R, true>>,
    },
    aliases?: Record<string, R>,                              // alias names cannot collide with route names
}
```

### Concrete examples from the test suite (`packages/core/tests/routing/route-map.spec.ts`):

```typescript
import { buildRouteMap } from "@stricli/core";

// Simple route map
const routeMap = buildRouteMap({
    routes: { doNothing: topCommand, sub: subRouteMap },
    docs: { brief: "route map brief" },
});

// With aliases
const routeMap = buildRouteMap({
    routes: { doNothing: command },
    docs: { brief: "route map brief" },
    aliases: { nothing: "doNothing" },
});

// With hidden routes
const routeMap = buildRouteMap({
    routes: { doNothing: topCommand, sub: subRouteMap },
    docs: {
        brief: "route map brief",
        hideRoute: { sub: true },
    },
});

// With default command
const routeMap = buildRouteMap({
    routes: { old: oldCommand, new: newCommand },
    defaultCommand: "old",
    docs: { brief: "route map brief" },
});
```

