The "file not found" error fires before the subagent check because we check existence first. Let me adjust - the subagent validation should happen before the existence check (or alongside it). Actually, looking at the code:

```typescript
async function resolveFromPath(filePath: string): Promise<SessionInfo> {
	const file = Bun.file(filePath);
	if (!(await file.exists())) {
		throw new Error(`Session file not found: ${filePath}`);
	}

	const filename = basename(filePath);
	validateNotSubagent(filename);
	...
```

The exists check happens first. But actually, the subagent validation should come first since we want to catch it even if the file exists. 

I'll reorder the checks so the subagent validation runs before checking if the file exists - that way we catch the subagent error first and give a more specific error message.

